    Addable<Message>, Appendable<Message>, Indexable<Message>, Prependable<Message>, Sequence<Message>, Receiver<Transmittable>, NamedObject, Countable, Sized, NewInstance<BaseList<Message>>, CompressibleCollection, AsString, Listener, MessageCounter, Transceiver, java.lang.Iterable<Message>, java.util.Collection<Message>, java.util.List<Message>, java.util.RandomAccess
    public class ValidationIssues
extends MessageList
    A MessageList and MessageCounter that captures validation issues. The number of issues of different types can be retrieved with MessageList.count(Class), passing in the type of message for which a count is desired. The method MessageList.countWorseThanOrEqualTo(Message.Status) gives a count of all messages that are at least as bad or worse than the given message status value. For example, countWorseThanOrEqualTo(Status.PROBLEM).
    Author:
    jonathanl (shibo)
